Package ohos.media.common.sessioncore

Class AVSessionCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.media.common.sessioncore.AVSessionCallback

  • public abstract class AVSessionCallback
extends Object
    Provides callbacks to control media playback. You can use AVSession.setAVSessionCallback(ohos.media.common.sessioncore.AVSessionCallback) to register callbacks to listen to media sessions.
    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Multimedia#MEDIA

    • Method Detail

      • onCommand

        public void onCommand​(String command,
                      PacMap options,
                      GeneralReceiver callback)
        Called when the ohos.media.sessioncore.AVController sends a command to the media session. The media session owner can process custom commands.
        Parameters:
        command - Indicates the command name.
        options - Indicates optional parameters of the command.
        callback - Indicates the callback that receives the execution result. This parameter can be null.

      • onMediaButtonEvent

        public boolean onMediaButtonEvent​(Intent mediaButtonIntent)
        Called when a button event is triggered and the media session has the highest priority, or when the AVController sends a button event to the session.
        Parameters:
        mediaButtonIntent - Indicates the intent that contains the AVSession.PARAM_KEY_EVENT field specifying a KeyEvent object, based on which playback is controlled. This intent is of the AVSession.ACTION_MEDIA_BUTTON type.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the key event in the intent has been processed; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        3

      • onPrepareToPlay

        public void onPrepareToPlay​()
        Called when the application is requested to prepare for playback.

        You can override this callback to handle the request. After the preparation is completed, the playback state should be changed to AVPlaybackState#PLAYBACK_STATE_PAUSED.

        Since:
        3

      • onPrepareToPlayByMediaId

        public void onPrepareToPlayByMediaId​(String mediaId,
                                     PacMap options)
        Called when the application is requested to prepare for playing the media item specified by the AVBrowserService.

        You can override this callback to handle the request. After the preparation is completed, the playback state should be changed to AVPlaybackState#PLAYBACK_STATE_PAUSED.

        Parameters:
        mediaId - Identifies the media item.
        options - Indicates additional information about the media item.
        Since:
        3

      • onPrepareToPlayBySearch

        public void onPrepareToPlayBySearch​(String query,
                                    PacMap options)
        Called when the application is requested to prepare for starting playback from a search result.

        You can override this callback to handle the request. After the preparation is completed, the playback state should be changed to AVPlaybackState#PLAYBACK_STATE_PAUSED.

        Parameters:
        query - Indicates the search criteria. If this parameter is null, the application can prepare for any media item.
        options - Indicates additional data to search for.
        Since:
        3

      • onPrepareToPlayByUri

        public void onPrepareToPlayByUri​(Uri uri,
                                 PacMap options)
        Called when the application is requested to prepare for playing the media item specified by a URI.

        You can override this callback to handle the request. After the preparation is completed, the playback state should be changed to AVPlaybackState#PLAYBACK_STATE_PAUSED.

        Parameters:
        uri - Indicates the media item URI.
        options - Indicates additional information about the media item.
        Since:
        3
